What was the Clinton Administration's policy on the Russian economy? The Clinton Administration's policy on the Russian economy was to encourage the development of a market economy and to promote private-sector investment.

Within the United Nations, real power is located in the Security Council. This is not universally agreed upon, as some argue that the General Assembly has more power. However, the Security Council is generally seen as having the most important role within the UN, as it has the ability to authorize the use of military force and to impose sanctions.
